<span id="freeTextContainer4628325200248928915">I am almost anti-fantasy. I find most derivative at best and banal to the extreme. Wolfe&apos;s first book in his famous <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/968868.The_Book_of_the_New_Sun' title='The Book of the New Sun by Gene Wolfe' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Book of the New Sun</a> tetralogy, however, is genre fiction at its finest. Original, difficult and well-crafted, it is easy to see how Wolfe is regarded as a writer&apos;s writer.</span>
  <span id="freeText4628325200248928915" style="display:none">I am almost anti-fantasy. I find most derivative at best and banal to the extreme. Wolfe's first book in his famous <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/968868.The_Book_of_the_New_Sun" title="The Book of the New Sun by Gene Wolfe" rel="nofollow noopener">The Book of the New Sun</a> tetralogy, however, is genre fiction at its finest. Original, difficult and well-crafted, it is easy to see how Wolfe is regarded as a writer's writer.</span>
