<div id="review_40352306" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/40352306" />
    <a title="Ryan Mishap" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1058994-ryan-mishap"><img alt="Ryan Mishap" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641147302p2/1058994.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/40352306?book_show_action=true">Dec 17, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ryan Mishap" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ryan Mishap" href="/user/show/1058994-ryan-mishap">Ryan Mishap</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1058994-ryan-mishap?shelf=garbage">garbage</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer40352306" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6626845917066230046">Okay, like many an SF book, this plunges us into a nebulous world not wholly rendered--in a grave yard no less. Now that&apos;s a good start: the protagonist encounters rebels in the graveyard robbin&apos; bones and then goes back to his guild. The Torturer&apos;s Guild, mind. From here, the book drags like a fucking stone weight around your brain as our would be torturer becomes obssessed with a captive and eventually leaves to find some other destiny. I got to the end after hundreds of pages and realized not</span>
  <span id="freeText6626845917066230046" style="display:none">Okay, like many an SF book, this plunges us into a nebulous world not wholly rendered--in a grave yard no less. Now that's a good start: the protagonist encounters rebels in the graveyard robbin' bones and then goes back to his guild. The Torturer's Guild, mind. From here, the book drags like a fucking stone weight around your brain as our would be torturer becomes obssessed with a captive and eventually leaves to find some other destiny. I got to the end after hundreds of pages and realized nothing really happened, the plot was dead in the water, and I didn't give a fuck about any of the characters. Hell if I'm going to read the other three books, Gene.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6626845917066230046" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


